00:33:59.505 --> 00:34:01.796
LIZ CUNNINGHAM: I just wanted
to add one point to that.

00:34:01.796 --> 00:34:03.950
I think they're all
brilliant initiatives, Mick,

00:34:03.950 --> 00:34:06.200
and I'd encourage everybody
to get involved with them.

00:34:06.200 --> 00:34:10.404
I think, particularly the
space people may struggle with,

00:34:10.404 --> 00:34:11.570
how they can have an impact.

00:34:11.570 --> 00:34:15.199
So we had our finance
directors and VPs offsite,

00:34:15.199 --> 00:34:18.110
and we had a talk from
the finance BGN group.

00:34:18.110 --> 00:34:22.610
And they were so
passionate about not

00:34:22.610 --> 00:34:23.920
being afraid to get involved.

00:34:23.920 --> 00:34:25.940
So people are
concerned in the space

00:34:25.940 --> 00:34:27.170
about doing the wrong thing.

00:34:27.170 --> 00:34:30.810
And it's so easy to say, well,
I'd rather not make a mistake,

00:34:30.810 --> 00:34:32.630
and so I'm not going
to get involved.

00:34:32.630 --> 00:34:36.860
And they were so encouraging
of the VP and director

00:34:36.860 --> 00:34:38.210
group that were there to--

00:34:38.210 --> 00:34:40.230
it's OK to make a mistake.

00:34:40.230 --> 00:34:41.510
It's OK.

00:34:41.510 --> 00:34:42.710
Even dipping your toe in.

00:34:42.710 --> 00:34:45.251
So while all these initiatives
are great, Mick, and I really,

00:34:45.251 --> 00:34:47.360
really encourage
people to get involved,

00:34:47.360 --> 00:34:51.320
just look within your own team,
and wider team, your neighbors

00:34:51.320 --> 00:34:55.880
around you, and see where you
can even make one small impact,

00:34:55.880 --> 00:34:58.470
and not to worry about
doing the wrong thing.

00:34:58.470 --> 00:35:01.670
Because doing something
means that you're

00:35:01.670 --> 00:35:02.840
making a difference.

00:35:02.840 --> 00:35:04.760
So that would be
my word of advice.

00:35:04.760 --> 00:35:06.080
RUTH HUNT: And Stonewall
